IQA Intraatomic ("Self") Energy Components:
------------------------------------------
  E_IQA_Intra(A) = T(A) + Vne(A,A) + Vee(A,A)
                 = Intraatomic ("Self") Contribution to E_IQA(A)
  T(A) = Electronic Kinetic Energy of Atom A (Hamiltonian Form)
  Vne(A,A) = Attraction Energy Between Electron Density Distribution of Atom A and Nucleus of Atom A
  Vee(A,A) = Two-electron Interaction Energy of Atom A With Itself
  VeeC(A,A) = Coulomb Part of Vee(A,A)
  VeeX(A,A) = Exchange-Correlation Part of Vee(A,A)
See "2EDM Note" and "DFT Note".
